title <size:18>Meeting Scheduler System (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Alice wants to schedule 1hr meeting with Bob, Charlie. System finds 3 common free slots, picks best one, sends invites."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE
' ====================================================================
class MeetingScheduler <<Facade>> {
    - calendarService : CalendarService
    - slotFinder : SlotFinder
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    - meetingRepository : MeetingRepository
    --
    + scheduleMeeting(request) : Meeting
    + findAvailableSlots(participants, duration, range) : List<TimeSlot>
    + cancelMeeting(meetingId) : void
    + rescheduleMeeting(meetingId, newSlot) : Meeting
    + respondToInvite(meetingId, userId, response) : void
    + getMeetingsForUser(userId, date) : List<Meeting>
}

note top of MeetingScheduler #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "Alice wants a 1hr meeting with Bob and Charlie
    sometime this week. Client calls
    findAvailableSlots(participants, 60min, thisWeek)
    -> gets 3 possible slots -> picks one ->
    scheduleMeeting(request) -> invites sent."

    "**Facade** hides: calendar lookups, slot finding
    algorithms, conflict detection, and notifications."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: PARTICIPANT + CALENDAR
' ====================================================================
class Participant {
    - userId : String
    - name : String
    - email : String
    - calendar : Calendar
    - timezone : String
    - workingHours : WorkingHours
    --
    + getCalendar() : Calendar
    + getWorkingHours() : WorkingHours
    + isAvailable(slot) : bool
}

class Calendar {
    - ownerId : String
    - events : List<CalendarEvent>
    --
    + addEvent(event) : void
    + removeEvent(eventId) : void
    + getEvents(date) : List<CalendarEvent>
    + getEvents(from, to) : List<CalendarEvent>
    + getFreeBusy(from, to) : List<FreeBusyBlock>
}

class CalendarEvent {
    - eventId : String
    - title : String
    - startTime : LocalDateTime
    - endTime : LocalDateTime
    - isAllDay : bool
    - recurrence : RecurrenceRule
    - status : EventStatus
    --
    + getTimeSlot() : TimeSlot
    + overlaps(slot) : bool
    + getDurationMinutes() : int
}

class WorkingHours {
    - startTime : LocalTime
    - endTime : LocalTime
    - workingDays : Set<DayOfWeek>
    --
    + isWorkingTime(dateTime) : bool
    + getWorkingSlot(date) : TimeSlot
}

enum EventStatus {
    CONFIRMED
    TENTATIVE
    CANCELLED
    OUT_OF_OFFICE
}

note top of Participant #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - Who is being scheduled?**
    "Each **Participant** has a **Calendar** with
    CalendarEvents and **WorkingHours**."

    "**Calendar.getFreeBusy(from, to):**
    Returns blocks of busy time in a range.
    This is the raw data the slot finder uses."

    "**WorkingHours**: 9am-6pm, Mon-Fri.
    Don't schedule meetings at 11pm or Sunday."

    "**CalendarEvent**: existing meetings with
